IPF Plans to List Shares on Warsaw Stock Exchange Next Year, Puls Reports

-- B y   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 
2011-07-22T05:04:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/ipf-plans-to-list-shares-on-warsaw-stock-exchange-next-year-puls-reports.html
International Personal Finance Plc (IPF) ,
a U.K. lender that makes unsecured loans to low-income
households overseas, plans to list shares on the  Warsaw Stock
Exchange  next year,  Puls Biznesu  reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer John Harnett.  IPF may debut on the Polish bourse in April or May, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Monika Rozlal in Warsaw at 
 mrozlal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at   bpenz@bloomberg.net . 